-- Elliott Urges Actelion Resignations in Push for Sale, Financial Times Says
-- B y   V i c t o r i a   R i c h a r d s
-- 2011-02-03T22:03:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/elliott-urges-actelion-resignations-in-push-for-sale-financial-times-says.html
Elliott Associates LP is pushing for
the resignations of  Actelion Ltd .’s Chief Executive Officer
Jean-Paul Clozel and Chairman Robert Cawthorn, the Financial
Times reported, citing a letter sent to directors by the hedge
fund and obtained by the FT. Elliott wants the formation of a
strategic committee to explore the company’s options on rumored
takeover approaches, the FT said, citing the letter.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Richards at 
 vrichards@bloomberg.net  